            <title>[DERBY-446] Client data source implementations cause security exception on storage to/from a Reference object</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-446</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The ClientBaseDataSource code to access the property value fields through reflection throws security exceptions as it trieds to disable security checks. Rather than requiring this somewhat dangerous permission, Derby client code can simply call the public getter and setter methods for the properties, with no security concerns,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using the test to be added in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-445&quot; title=&quot;Client data sources lose the value of the connectionAttributes property when they are stored using the Reference interface&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-445&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-445&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
